Ashton Wood will read out a 'not sorry' apology to Jeep on the ABC tonight . 
  The car company requested he apologise for criticising them  . 
  Mr Wood raised $18,000 to destroy his car after Jeep refused to pay a full refund or replace the vehicle . 
  He claimed the Jeep Cherokee had 21 separate mechanical problems . 
  Jeep requested he publish the apology in a national publication . 
  Mr Wood will instead read it out on 'The Checkout' tonight . 
  He is campaigning for the United States' Lemon Laws to be introduced in Australia . 
  In June last year he and 300 people destroyed his car . 
 